><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Horsie speed and info</span><hr size=1> Paid around 31k for my second tier black with 145 charisma.<br>
<br>
It feels somewhere just below sow to me, but I have no pie chart or anything to prove it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
One really nice thing about the horse is the greatly reduced falling damage.  I generally take no damage from falling unless it's a huge drop.  For example, jumping down the chasm to ToV would have killed me before, now I take around 500 damage.<br>
<br>
Fighting on a horse is very cumbersome as a melee.  You can't slam but you can kick.  You can't bandage.  The horse moves about slowly unless you are running full tilt.  It's certainly possible to fight on one, but I find it too annoying to bother usually.<br>
<br>
The color changes the price just because certain colors are more popular.  Who wants a tan horse?<br>
<br>
To sum up, if I were to buy a horse knowing what I know now, I'd save for the best.  Being able to travel through worthless outdoor zones that fast with no falling damage would be quite nice. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubelarios.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Belarios</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/14/01 5:05:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9065.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Horsie speed and info</span><hr size=1> Loving my brown chain horsie.  Much faster than jboots, plus safe fall for crossing hilly terrain, plus mediation so you get mana back at your sitting rate while traveling.  I only wish that you could switch off the bouncing...I think the camera movement is making me ill...<br>
